## 0.1.76

- Rolls forward to xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.161: phy-managed DDMI polling
  cadence relaxed from every monitor tick (~5 s) to every 6 monitor
  ticks (~30 s).  Same readings, ~6× less fork+exec / I²C churn on
  hosts with many SFP ports.

## 0.1.75

- Rolls forward to xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.160: **SFP DDMI optical readings
  now work on Ubuntu 22.04 / ethtool 5.16 hosts**.  Previously
  `show physical interface <name>` on a FIBRE port displayed only SFP
  identity (vendor / PN / SN) because Ubuntu's ethtool refuses to
  decode the A2 DDM page into text output.  xcespproc now reads the
  raw 512-byte EEPROM via `ethtool -m <dev> hex on` and decodes the
  optical readings (Rx/Tx dBm, temperature, voltage, bias) per SFF-8472
  on the C++ side.  No-op on Fedora 41+ / Ubuntu 24.04+ (newer ethtool
  decodes natively).

## 0.1.74

